The full text of the agreement -has been kept secret for some time -it has been submitted to Papua New Guinea Parliament on Wednesday night, allowing its details to be disclosed.

After reaching an agreement with Papua New Guinea in the Southwest Pacific, the United States will be able to station troops and ships at the major airports, except for the Ronbugnem Base on the island of Manus and a port of the capital of the capital Mozby.

This agreement provides the right to grant Washington's "pre -reserve" place "pre -reserves of equipment, supplies, and ammunition", as well as the rights of "construction activities" in the "exclusive use" base.

