Entering the Longbulum Naval Base can be used to strengthen the facilities of the United States in Guam in the north, which may be the key to conflict in Taiwan.

Facing the wave of protests accusing the authorities of abandoning national sovereignty, Prime Minister James Malape was forced to defend the agreement.

James Malape told the parliament on Wednesday evening, "In the past 48 years, we allowed our army to weaken," he emphasized, "sovereignty depends on the stability and strength of the army."

