Papua New Guinea is rich in natural resources and close to major routes, which has become the main key to Washington and Beijing's diplomatic deadlock.

On the other hand, former Prime Minister Peter O'Neal said the agreement made Papua New Guinea a goal.

O'Neal said, "The United States does this to protect its national interests," he also added, "We all know the geopolitics that are happening in our region."

US President Biden originally scheduled to visit Papua New Guinea, but canceled his visit due to the US Congress's budget disputes.

After taking similar measures in Beijing, Washington is trying to fight for the support of the Pacific countries through a series of diplomatic and fiscal incentives in exchange for strategic support.

Chinese companies poured into the mines and ports across the Pacific Ocean. Last year, China and the Solomon Islands of neighboring countries signed a secret security agreement to allow them to deploy troops in the country.

The United States is concerned that the Chinese army's foothold in the South Pacific may surround its facilities in Guam, which makes the situation more complicated when regaining Taiwan in China.

