![](Images/cnnytimes/2023-06-16T10-37-23-08-00/15russia-china-03-vqkb-master1050.jpg)St. Petersburg Economic Forum, on Wednesday. SEFA KARACAN/Anadolu Agency, VIA Getty Images

The event was previously displayed to the Russian market to Europe and the United States. This year's forums cannot be seen on high -level managers in the West. The theme of this forum is the "de -US dollar" of global trade and the economic potential of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization. Russia and China are members of this regional organization.

However, compared with the past few years, China has not made a lineup in this forum. This seems to be part of Beijing's efforts to avoid being regarded as a war that is willing to support Putin.

The main Chinese guests who plan to attend the forum are the heads of the Chinese ambassador to Russia and the head of a trade delegation. [Xi Jinping himself](https://www.nytimes.com/2019/06/07/business/economy/russia-china-us-trade.html)He attended the 2019 forum, and he and Putin publicized the China and Russia on that forum to defend global free trade. Many Chinese executives and officials also attended that forum.

Although the Sino -Russian trade has increased by 41%in the first five months of this year, Chinese companies are cautious about investing in Russia. This is largely due to the risk of being punished by the Western government, especially since the Russian and Ukraine War.

